Single gendered washrooms, lockable, and in the back. Should be good to enter in your correct gender
comment: You should be an ordering and paying customer to use the washroom.

name: SilverCity Polo Park
directions:
There's two on each side, on the side with the higher numbers, there is a single use room in the middle of the corridor, on the left side.

The other one, the side with the lower numbers, the single use washroom is at the end of the corridor, left hand side.
comment:
If my directions aren't clear to you, you can ask one of the staff if there's a Family Restroom nearby and they can point it out to you.
You are most likely going to need to be seeing a movie in order to use these specific washrooms, as their locations are hard to sneak around the workers

name: Polo Park Shopping Center
directions:
There's a family washroom in the food court, second floor, right across from Tutti Frutti, near the parking lot doors.

Another family washroom is on the first floor, hidden between a jewelry store and a phone company, and in between a men's washroom and women's washroom.
comment: Both the family washrooms don't have doors to close, other than the stall doors, so be safe, and I wouldn't recommend waiting in line with families if there is a line up; most of the people who go there are impatient. Good luck!

name: Johnson C. Smith University

comment: Generally only open to the JCSU community or those with business on campus.
